Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @Breadcrumbs{25%g}, @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet} and the @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb. Set the crumb aside.

When your pan of water is boiling, stir in the @Macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Melt in the @Butter{20%g}.

Once the oil is hot, fry the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @Plain Flour{1.5%tbsp} and cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @Water{200%ml} for the sauce a little at a time, followed by the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} and @Vegetable Stock Paste{15%g}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat, then stir through the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}, Cheddar, @Fresh Pesto{32%g}, @Peas{120%g} and cooked macaroni.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Transfer the creamy pasta to an #ovenproof dish{} and top evenly with the herby crumb.

Place your mac and cheese on a #baking tray{} and grill until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Share your pesto bacon mac and cheese between your plates. Enjoy!